SIMPLE: monthly
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Monthly
<hw>Month"ly</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Continued a month, or
a performed in a month; <as>as, the <ex>monthly</ex> revolution of the
moon</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Done, happening, payable, published, etc., once a
month, or every month; <as>as, a <ex>monthly</ex> visit;
<ex>monthly</ex> charges; a <ex>monthly</ex> installment; a
<ex>monthly</ex> magazine.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Monthly nurse</b></col>, <cd>a nurse who serves for a
month or some short time, esp. one which attends women after
childbirth.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Monthly</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Monthly
<hw>Month"ly</hw>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it> <plw>Monthlies</plw>
<pr>(<?/)</pr>.</plu> <def>A publication which appears regularly once a
month.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Monthly</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Monthly
<hw>Month"ly</hw>, <pos>adv.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Once a month; in
every month; <as>as, the moon changes <ex>monthly</ex></as>.</def>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>As if under the influence of the moon; in the manner
of a lunatic.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Middleton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Monticle</ent>⟦br⟧
